Goal: build and verify FSCRUD-01 from a direct local-model prompt

memory:
  fscrud_workspace
  fscrud_task

flow:
  remember key="fscrud_workspace" value="workspace/fscrud-01"
  remember key="fscrud_task" value="TASK.md"

  run: node -e "const fs=require('fs'); fs.mkdirSync('workspace/fscrud-01',{recursive:true});" [timeout 60]
  let task_contract = "FSCRUD-01 field-service work order tracker. Build customers, assets, and work_orders with list/create/read/edit/detail/delete flows; enforce customer-asset-work_order references, asset/customer mismatch rejection, completedAt/status rules, safe deletes, seed data, domain validation tests, integration-style tests for each entity family, README, run-manifest.json, and verification-report.md. Prefer a small deterministic Node/Jest implementation with src/domain.js, src/server.js, and __tests__/domain.test.js before adding extra framework weight. Full task source is TASK.md."

  prompt: Work only in ${fscrud_workspace}. Read ${fscrud_task} before editing. Task contract: ${task_contract}. Build a full-stack CRUD app with customers, assets, and work orders. Include validation, relationship integrity, UI list/create/edit/detail/delete flows, seed data, tests, README, run manifest, and verification report. Minimum files before stopping: package.json, README.md, run-manifest.json, verification-report.md, src/domain.js, src/server.js, and __tests__/domain.test.js. Run install, test, and build or typecheck if available before stopping. Do not read or modify hidden verifier files. Local inference can be slow; prioritize correct, complete, verifiable work over speed.

done when:
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/package.json
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/README.md
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/run-manifest.json
  file_exists workspace/fscrud-01/verification-report.md
